article.headline: East Carolina earns 72-55 victory over UIC
article.description: — C.J. Walker and RJ Felton both had 21 points to help East Carolina defeat UIC 72-55 on Saturday.
article.linkText: East Carolina earns 72-55 victory over UIC
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. -- — C.J. Walker and RJ Felton both had 21 points to help East Carolina defeat UIC 72-55 on Saturday. Walker also added eight rebounds for the Pirates (6-1). Felton went 9 of 14 from the field (3 for 4 from 3-point range. Joran Riley shot 6 of 10 from the field and 1 for 3 from the line to finish with 13 points. Sasa Ciani led the Flames (4-3) in scoring, finishing with 10 points and eight rebounds. Ahmad Henderson II added 10 points for UIC. Modestas Kancleris finished with nine points and four blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
